description:
&lt;p&gt;Newham University Hospital is part of Bartshealth, which is the 4th largest Acute Trust in the UK. It serves the second fastest growing population in London. The newly built Rainbow Centre provides the environment for the Childrens Inpatient, Daycare and Outpatient Services delivered at Newham. The Childrens Services at Newham, is the only Bartshealth Childrens Service that has been rated as “Good” for all five domains by the Care Quality Commission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Rainbow Centre opened in 2017 and provides a bright, child friendly environment for children and young people from birth to 16years.It is fully equipped with new modern equipment, allowing care to be delivered to variety of medical, surgical and specialist conditions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the investment in developing services for children and young people at NUH, we have some exciting new opportunities for qualified nurses at Band 6 &amp; Band 5. As a new staff member , you will be supported by the Matron, Ward Manager &amp; Professional Development Nurse to progress and improve your clinical skills. There are many learning &amp; development opportunities for you within &lt;strong&gt;Our&lt;/strong&gt; lively forward thinking unit. We welcome new and innovative ideas as we develop our services to meet local needs and move to “Outstanding”.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
